        Call this method to do disambiguation.
        Parameters:
        gaz - the loaded Gazetteer
        labels - the MutableTextLabels used for disambiguation
        name - the Span which corresponds to the location name requiring disambiguation
        active - a boolean array, decides what modules shall be used for disambiguation
        Returns:
        an instance of Class Location or null, if disambiguation is not successful

      • checkAdjacent

        private static java.util.List<Location> checkAdjacent(Gazetteer gaz,
                                     java.util.List<Location> candi,
                                     edu.cmu.minorthird.text.MutableTextLabels labels,
                                     edu.cmu.minorthird.text.Span name)

        Module two: checks the adjacent context of the target location name; more specifically, checks if succeeding token(s) is the higher political district containing the target location name.

        For example, if "Ottawa" is followed by "Ontario", only candidates with a higher political district named "Ontario" will be kept.

        After this module, if there remains only 1 candidate, terminate disambiguation and return this candidate; otherwise, go to the next activated module

        Parameters:
        gaz -
        candi -
        labels -
        name -
        Returns:
